","additional_course":false,"affiliation_labels":[]},{"metrics":[{"metric_key":"points","metric_numeric":572}],"team_id":null,"result_id":"019d0f21-20ea-7238-a330-93a0371cfde2","time_text":"00:44:10","competitive":true,"course_rank":8,"status_code":"OK","affiliations":[],"outcome_text":"00:44:10","overall_rank":8,"result_notes":null,"category_name":null,"category_rank":null,"individual_id":"019d0a40-c419-7854-977c-7330d14c57d0","metric_summary":"Points 572","competitor_name":"Arbella Bet-Shlimon","competitor_type":"individual","additional_course":false,"affiliation_labels":[]}],"course_id":"019d0f21-2179-77cd-b9c9-dc5370eec9e6","course_name":"Open Women","distance_km":null,"result_count":8,"control_count":null,"course_climb_m":null},{"results":[{"metrics":[],"team_id":null,"result_id":"019d0f21-20ea-77aa-b9c9-992bb05978d0","time_text":"00:36:53","competitive":true,"course_rank":null,"status_code":"OK","affiliations":[],"outcome_text":"00:36:53","overall_rank":1,"result_notes":null,"category_name":"Advanced-Group","category_rank":1,"individual_id":"019d0a11-4d31-7579-aaa8-34aa739264b8","metric_summary":null,"competitor_name":"Tim Potter","competitor_type":"individual","additional_course":false,"affiliation_labels":[]}],"course_id":"019d0f21-2179-75fb-908b-38daa60968da","course_name":"Overall","distance_km":null,"result_count":1,"control_count":null,"course_climb_m":null}],"event_id":"019b81f3-1f4d-7fd4-be35-23de9ea19bf9","venue_id":"019b81f3-1f39-71e4-af69-aaadb4cfe14e","event_date":"2017-04-08","event_kind":"race","event_name":"Ultimate Series #4 - Sprint","venue_name":"North Seattle College","event_notes":null,"course_count":9,"event_status":null,"result_count":62,"citation_count":3,"event_comments":"The Ultimate Orienteer series is the sampler pack of orienteering: each event gives you the opportunity to try a different flavor!\nThe fourth event in the series is: THE SPRINT!\nA sprint is a relatively short race, but it’s about more than distance. A sprint challenges your ability to make quick decisions while under pressure. It may take you just 30 seconds to get from one control to the next, so you won’t want to spend 10 seconds standing still, deciding which way to go. In sprint orienteering, it’s Go Go Go!\nIf one sprint race is not enough to get your fix, stick around for the relay in the afternoon!\nWelcome to North Seattle College – Site for the Sprint and Two Person Relay! If you haven’t been here before, this is one of our more technical maps, with two levels of buildings to navigate. It’s also a relatively small area, so be sure to check your description sheets carefully – between the two events, there are a lot of controls.\nThe most unique feature of NSC is its two-story campus. The shapes of the buildings do vary between the stories, with the first floor denoted by dotted lines. You’ll need to think ahead to avoid getting stuck on the wrong level. Our intent was to make finding the best routes tricky, but to avoid any “gotcha” legs.\nThe southeastern parking lot appears to be home to some construction work at the moment. This should not affect any route choices, but the lot is not as empty as a college parking lot might usually be on a Saturday.\nSome of the longer courses will pay a visit to nearby Licton Springs Park, which involves a short sidewalk run. Please observe traffic laws, and cross only at the intersections that are not marked out-of-bounds. The out-of-bounds area is marked with red vertical lines and it is important to note that observing allowed crossing points in advance will be a key to success. On campus, the out of bounds areas for landscaping and private areas are in olive green.\nWhen we were designing the courses, the north end of the map was experiencing flooding. Bring an extra pair of socks for the drive home, and assume that any seasonal water features will be very wet.","external_links":[{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/event/ultimate-orienteer-4-sprint-2/","link_type":"event_page"},{"